# t/research/memory-restart-safety.test — the memory harvest is crash-safe
# (docs/03), the memory sibling of crash-before-send's outbox. A finished run's
# out/memory/ writes are recovered even when the capture-memory effect never
# completes inline.
#
# agent-run-finished no longer emits capture-memory as a Cmd — a crash between
# logging that message and the effect finishing would lose the harvest forever
# (replay re-derives the Cmd but SUPPRESSES effects, and the remember was never
# logged). Instead it records the run as a PENDING job on the tasks model. The
# harvest-reconcile subscription turns each pending job into capture-memory; the
# effect ends by emitting mark-harvested, which clears the job. A crash mid-harvest
# leaves the job pending, and restart's replay rebuilds it so the source fires
# again — exactly the guarantee email's pending outbox gives an unsent reply.
#
# This proves the FULL crash window, not just quiescence: the harvest's
# ProvisionedMemory read is faulted so the effect errors before emitting anything,
# the process crashes with the job still owed, and the restart recovers it.

send allow-sender { address kasi@decode.ee }

# The harvest's ProvisionedMemory read will fail on its first attempt (only
# capture-memory reads it, so this fails the harvest and nothing else)...
fail work harvest

deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "banking"
    body    "note the owner's banking setup for future payments"
}
task 1 status is awaiting-agent

# ...so when the agent finishes, the harvest-reconcile source drives capture-memory
# but the effect errors before emitting: nothing is remembered, and the
# mark-harvested that would clear the job never comes.
agent {
    out reply.txt                "Noted the banking setup."
    out memory/owner-banking.md  [fixture memory/owner-banking.md]
}
task 1 status is awaiting-user

# The reply still sent — the harvest is orthogonal to delivery.
outbound count is 1

# The harvest did NOT land: the collection is empty...
model memory memories is ""
# ...and the run sits in the pending set, still owed a harvest. This is the crash
# window: the fact would be lost forever if HarvestPending were not logged state.
model tasks harvest_pending matches "*run_id*"

# The process dies and comes back: full-log replay rebuilds HarvestPending, then the
# harvest-reconcile subscription re-fires — this time ProvisionedMemory succeeds.
crash
restart

task 1 status is awaiting-user                    # replay rebuilt the model
memory owner-banking matches "*Handelsbanken*"    # the harvest was recovered
memory owner-banking description matches "*never reuse an OCR across invoices*"
model tasks harvest_pending is ""                 # mark-harvested cleared it — exactly once
